@startuml User Authentication Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline

title User Authentication Flow

actor "User" as User
participant "Login Form" as Form
participant "REST API" as API
participant "CommandBus" as CmdBus
participant "AuthenticateUserHandler" as Handler
participant "AuthenticationService" as AuthSvc
participant "UserRepository" as UserRepo
participant "SessionRepository" as SessionRepo
participant "PasswordPolicyService" as PasswordPolicy
participant "PrismaClient" as Prisma
participant "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Redis" as Redis
participant "EventBus" as EventBus

== Login Request ==
User -> Form: Enter credentials\n(username, password)
Form -> API: POST /api/auth/login\n{\n  "username": "john",\n  "password": "secret123"\n}
API -> CmdBus: AuthenticateUserCommand

== Command Processing ==
CmdBus -> Handler: handle(command)
Handler -> AuthSvc: authenticate(credentials)

== User Lookup ==
AuthSvc -> UserRepo: findByUsername(username)
UserRepo -> Prisma: SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = ?
Prisma -> DB: Query execution
DB --> Prisma: User record
Prisma --> UserRepo: User entity
UserRepo --> AuthSvc: User

== Password Validation ==
AuthSvc -> PasswordPolicy: validatePassword(password, user.hash)
PasswordPolicy -> PasswordPolicy: bcrypt.compare()
PasswordPolicy --> AuthSvc: password valid

== Session Creation ==
AuthSvc -> AuthSvc: generate tokens
AuthSvc -> SessionRepo: create(userId, ipAddress)
SessionRepo -> Redis: SET session:{id} user_data
Redis --> SessionRepo: OK

== Event Publishing ==
AuthSvc -> EventBus: publish(UserAuthenticatedEvent)

== Response ==
AuthSvc --> Handler: AuthenticationResult\n{\n  accessToken,\n  refreshToken,\n  user\n}
Handler --> CmdBus: success
CmdBus --> API: 200 OK\n{\n  "accessToken": "...",\n  "refreshToken": "...",\n  "user": {...}\n}
API --> Form: tokens + user data
Form --> User: Login successful

== Token Storage ==
Form -> Form: store tokens in localStorage

== Subsequent Requests ==
note over User, API
    Future API calls include:
    Authorization: Bearer {accessToken}
end note

@enduml
